   SERIAL-KILLER-SURVIVOR (Lexington, Ky.) _ Of the eight murder
cases now linked to alleged serial killer Rafael Resendez-Ramirez,
only one includes an eyewitness. A look at what happened near the
University of Kentucky campus on Aug. 29, 1997, and the woman who
lived to tell about it. By LISA TEACHEY.
</P>
<P>
   BIDI-CIGARETTES (Albany, N.Y.) _ Sitting on a bicycle outside
Albany High School, the 16-year-old student unfolded his wallet and
plucked out one of the thin, flavored cigarettes that are gaining
popularity among Capital Region teenagers. The hand-rolled,
unfiltered butts _ called bidis, or beedies _ release two or three
times the nicotine and tar of regular cigarettes. Yet many people,
including this teenager, think they are cleaner than the average
smoke. By EDWARD FITZPATRICK
</P>
<P>
   BIDIS-Q&AMP;A (Undated) _ Q: Are bidis safer than regular
cigarettes?
</P>
<P>
   A: Despite containing less tobacco than a U.S. cigarette, an
unfiltered bidi releases at least two to three times more tar and
nicotine.
</P>
<P>
   VATICAN-COLLEGES (Albany, N.Y.) _ Six months after U.S. bishops
called for closer ties between Catholic colleges and the Vatican,
the proclamation's most visible legacy is paper _ lots of it. The
paper trail is testament to the substantial confusion surrounding a
papal document called ``Ex corde Ecclesiae,'' or ``From the Heart
of the Church.'' By ANDREW BROWNSTEIN.
</P>
