</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    `Quiet, Wyatt!'
 &HT;    By Theresa Walsh Giarrusso
 &HT;    c.1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ If you feel like nobody ever listens and nobody ever
thinks you're old enough to do anything, you need to read about
Wyatt. ``Quiet, Wyatt!'' by Bill Maynard (G.P. Putnam's Sons,
$15.99) is a new book about a little boy who's determined to teach
his whole town a lesson _ he matters, too! Great for younger
readers, the book is easy to follow and has colorful illustrations.
</P>
<P>
   Chipper shows off his swing
</P>
<P>
   Slammin' Sammy Sosa may be the cover boy for Sports Illustrated
for Kids, but we want to read about Chipper Jones. The Braves'
third baseman is in the July issue teaching us how to switch-hit.
There are great action shots and step-by-step instructions. He also
offers other batting tips. The issue is available for $2.95.
</P>
