<P>
   TECHNOLOGY
</P>
<P>
   COXNET PTECH PAGE
</P>
<P>
   EDS: This is the CoxNet PTECH page for the current week. This
layout is available Tuesday after 2 p.m.
</P>
<P>
   CoxNet PTECH 0629 _ SENIORS _ Like many seniors, Mollie Newman
was slow to join the PC revolution. ``I thought maybe it would be
too difficult for me to learn how to use it,'' the 75-year-old
Austinite said last week. ``I felt like I wouldn't be too
interested.'' No more. In January, on her 75th birthday, Newman
bought a Dell Dimension model and signed up for a computer class
from SeniorNet, a nationwide, nonprofit program designed to make
older Americans comfortable with a computer. (Mahoney, Austin
American-Statesman) WITH PHOTOS
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
