</P>
<P>
   (Villard, $19.95.) Reflections on politics, pro
</P>
<P>
   wrestling and other subjects by the governor of
</P>
<P>
   Minnesota.
</P>
<P>
   9. COMRADES, by Stephen E. Ambrose. (Simon &AMP; Schuster,
</P>
<P>
   $21.) A celebration of male friendships by the historian
</P>
<P>
   and biographer.
</P>
<P>
   10. ENCORE PROVENCE, by Peter Mayle. (Knopf, $23.)
</P>
<P>
   The author of ``A Year in Provence'' recounts further
</P>
<P>
   adventures in the south of France.
</P>
<P>
   11. THE ART OF HAPPINESS, by the Dalai Lama and Howard
</P>
<P>
   C. Cutler. (Riverhead, $22.95.) What Buddhist doctrines
</P>
<P>
   and common sense tell us about dealing with everyday
</P>
<P>
   problems.
</P>
<P>
   12. BETRAYAL, by Bill Gertz. (Regnery, $27.95.)
</P>
<P>
   A reporter charges that the Clinton administration
</P>
<P>
   has undermined America's security. (b)
</P>
<P>
   13. ALL TOO HUMAN, by George Stephanopoulous. (Little,
</P>
<P>
   Brown, $27.95.) The former adviser to President Clinton
</P>
<P>
   recalls his years in the White House.
</P>
<P>
   14.(x) A GOLFER'S LIFE, by Arnold Palmer with James
</P>
<P>
   Dodson. (Ballantine, $26.95.) The autobiography of golf's
</P>
<P>
   most charismatic champion.
</P>
<P>
