<DOCNO> NYT19990628.0152 </DOCNO>
<DOCTYPE> MISCELLANEOUS TEXT (slug-filter) </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-06-28 13:09 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A1945 &Cx1f; ttj-z
r a &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-BIDIS-Q&AMP;A-HNS &LR;      06-28 0290
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BIDIS-Q&AMP;A-HNS </SLUG>
  
 (For use by New York Times News Service clients.)  
 c.1999 Albany Times Union  
<TEXT>
<P>
   Q: Are bidis safer than regular cigarettes?
</P>
<P>
   A: Bidis consist of thin, sun-dried flakes or strands of tobacco
wrapped up in the leaf of the tendu plant. Despite containing less
tobacco than a U.S. cigarette, an unfiltered bidi releases at least
two to three times more tar and nicotine. The tendu leaves are not
porous, which means the smoker must inhale often and deeply to keep
them lit, resulting in the absorption of especially large
quantities of tar, nicotine and carbon monoxide. This inhalation
may result in increased chance of smoking-related diseases.
</P>
<P>
   Q: Are clove cigarettes safer than regular cigarettes?
</P>
<P>
   A: Clove cigarettes, imported from Indonesia, contain 60 percent
to 70 percent tobacco and 30 percent to 40 percent ground cloves,
clove oil and other additives. Clove cigarettes have nicotine, tar
and carbon monoxide yields that are twice as high as moderate-tar
cigarettes. Users of clove cigarettes have reported ailments
ranging from nosebleeds to asthma attacks. Clove cigarettes contain
eugenol, which numbs the throat and suppresses the cough reflex.
</P>
<P>
   Q: Are additive-free cigarettes safer than regular cigarettes?
</P>
<P>
   A: ``Removing the additives from cigarettes does not remove the
nicotine, the tars or any of the other constituents of tobacco,''
said Dudley Hafner, chief executive officers of the American Heart
Association. ``Burning tobacco and ingesting it into the lungs is
responsible for the deaths of more than 400,000 Americans each
year. With or without additives, cigarettes can hurt you.''
</P>
<P>
   SOURCE: Centers for Disease Control and Prevention, Office on
Smoking and Health
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
