A1971 &Cx1f; ttx-z
r e &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-FILM-SMITH-SANDLER-TE     06-28 0604
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FILM-SMITH-SANDLER-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
GORE VS. BUSH? WHO CARES?
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By MALCOLM MAYHEW 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Gore vs. Bush? Who cares?
</P>
<P>
   The real race of the summer is the battle between Smith and
Sandler.
</P>
<P>
   Both Will Smith and Adam Sandler have new movies to tout, so
both are gunning for your vote at the box office.
</P>
<P>
   Here's a look at both candidates.
</P>
<P>
   The candidate: Will Smith
</P>
<P>
   Personal stats: Age: 30. Birth date: Sept. 25, 1968, in Philly.
</P>
<P>
   Current campaign offering: ``Wild Wild West,'' Smith's upgrade
of the old TV series about a James Bond type battling Old American
West evil. Opens Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
   Running mate: WWW co-star Kevin Kline.
</P>
<P>
   Political style: He'll charm you into voting for him. Don't, and
he'll kick your butt.
</P>
<P>
   Campaign slogan: ``A vote for me is a vote to get jiggy.''
</P>
<P>
   Campaign platform: Promises free Will Smith CDs with every
purchase of a movie ticket _ has to be one of his movies, though.
</P>
<P>
   Family values: Has a son from a previous marriage, William
``Trey'' Smith III. Smith's recent hit, ``Just the Two of Us,'' is
a tribute to him. Awwww. Smith married actress Jada Pinkett, 27, on
New Year's Eve '97; the couple's first kiddo, Jaden Christopher
Syre Smith, arrived a year ago.
</P>
<P>
   Fund-raising ability: Uh-oh. Sandler's the favored choice in
this category: Smith's last pic, ``Enemy of the State,'' made
around $60 mil, about half of what Sandler's last movie, ``The
Waterboy,'' took in. You can still bank on Smith, though: He was
the driving force behind blockbusters ``Men in Black'' and
``Independence Day.''
</P>
<P>
   Formative years: Smith honed his acting abilities on the
often-funny TV series ``Fresh Prince of Bel-Aire.''
</P>
<P>
   Baggage: Nothing too bad: He was one-half of a really lame rap
act, Fresh Prince and Jazzy Jeff. Oh, yeah, and his ``Fresh
Prince'' wardrobe _ loud, mismatched colors, baggier than Walter
Matthau's face _ was heinous. Thankfully, he became one of two
``Men in Black.''
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   The candidate: Adam Sandler
</P>
<P>
   Personal stats: Age: 32. Birth date: Sept. 9, 1966, in Brooklyn.
</P>
<P>
   Current campaign offering: ``Big Daddy.'' Wisecracker Sandler
suddenly has to father a little boy. Chaos ensues. Ha, ha.
</P>
<P>
   Running mate: Cole and Dylan Sprouse, the twin kiddo co-stars of
``Big Daddy.''
</P>
<P>
   Political style: Shy but cheeky; he'd propose a bill that would
make it illegal for women to wear bras, but he'd be too meek to
defend it in court.
</P>
<P>
   Campaign slogan: (Sung to the tune of his hit ``The Chanuka
Song'') ``Please, please vote for me-akah/Then I can get my own
Monica.''
</P>
<P>
   Campaign platform: Would make sure every issue of TV Guide
included a page of bathroom jokes.
</P>
<P>
   Family values: Never been married, but just got engaged to model
Jackie Titone, 24. Gets points for once dating Alicia Silverstone.
I'll vote for ya, Adam, if you give me her number.
</P>
<P>
   Fund-raising ability: Sandler's last movie, ``The Waterboy,''
raked in more than $130 million. Resume also includes ``Happy
Gilmore,'' ``Billy Madison'' and the sweet romance ``The Wedding
Singer.''
</P>
<P>
   Formative years: First taste of Hollywood: a small role on ``The
Cosby Show,'' playing a friend of Theo. Anyone 'member that?
Sandler got his real start on ``Saturday Night Live,'' playing the
role of cute dunderheads like Cajun Man and Opera Man; he also made
a name for himself as a dangerously hilarious stand-up comedian. We
love his funny songs, too.
</P>
<P>
   Baggage: In high school, he had a really big 'fro. Really big.
</P>
<P>
   (Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide
Web: www.star-telegram.com) &QL; 
nn
</P>
</TEXT>
