<SLUG> BC-FAMILY-VACATION-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
EIGHT IDEAS TO TAKE THE EDGE OFF THE FAMILY ROAD TRIP
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By ALYSON WARD 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Traveling with the family on the blazing-hot highway should be a
part of every kid's summer plans. Sure, all that togetherness in
the family truckster can wear on your nerves, but what better way
is there to bond? To help you survive the time in the car, we
rounded up the best of the new family-friendly,
stop-the-fracas-in-the-backseat stuff in town.
</P>
<P>
   1. You've seen those talking globes that test you with geography
questions. Now they've been miniaturized for travel. The
Educational Insights GeoSafari Talking Globe Traveler for kids 8
and up will keep your kids' brains from turning to mush as the
miles fly by. The globe will ask more than 5,000 questions _ Is
Portugal a country? Where is Nairobi? _ and can be held in the palm
of your offspring's hand. Available at toy stores. $50-$60.
</P>
<P>
   2. Fidget and fiddle for a good reason: Make shapes out of
Rainbow Twist Cubes, about a dozen brightly colored wooden blocks
on a stretchy string. They're entertaining for 4-year-olds and
addled adults alike. Produced by Pappa Gepetto's Toys, Rainbow
Twist Cubes can be bought for $6 (three-inch), and $11.50
(five-inch).
</P>
<P>
   3. Stop arguing over the radio station and try some new music
that has a chance of pleasing the whole family. ``For Our Children
Too!'' features family favorites sung by adult contemporary
performers: Luther Vandross sings ``If I Had a Hammer,'' Celine
Dion performs ``Brahms' Lullaby'' and Faith Hill sings ``Over the
Rainbow.'' If the music isn't your thing, be comforted by the fact
that proceeds from the CD benefit the Pediatric AIDS Foundation. If
you want something new instead of old standbys, ``Reggae for Kids''
introduces the upbeat music with songs that appeal to children.
Tapes are $12-$13 and CDs are $18-$19.
</P>
<P>
   4. Buy your kids disposable cameras and make them the trip
historians. Check out the Photo Fun! Vacation kit, a box full of
supplies to send postcards from the road and put vacation photos on
display. The kit comes with caption stickers, a hot-pink inflatable
picture frame, and a memory album for storing pictures and
souvenirs. Made by Photoco; available for about $15.
</P>
<P>
   5. Traveling with toddlers? The spill-proof Snack-Up Cup holds
11 ounces, and a compartment attached to the bottom holds a small
snack. The cup keeps everything in one place and, with any luck,
keeps grape juice from getting all over the car. From The First
Years; available at discount and toy stores for about $6.
</P>
<P>
   6. Your car will collect clutter. It just will. To control the
chaos, cram toys, papers, snacks and tissues into the pockets of an
organizer attached to the back of the front seat. This can be used
for trip necessities or as an activity center for kids, and it will
provide at least the illusion of order. We saw versions we liked
for $10-$12.
</P>
<P>
   7. Reduce the whining by keeping kids comfy. Toddlers can sleep
in their car seats with a wrap-around cushion that will protect
their necks. For about the same price, you can find an adult-size
neck cushion, but only the children's cushions from The First Years
have Sesame Street characters. Available at toy and discount
stores. Approximate price: $10.
</P>
<P>
   8. Travel activity books published by Klutz Press are a favorite
with kids and parents. ``The Amazing Backseat Book-a-ma-Thing''
promises ``thousands of miles' worth of hands-on games and
activities'' and contains everything from a pinball baseball game
to an acetate-sheet Magic Writer. ``The Etch A Sketch Book''
contains a mini-Etch A Sketch and pages of suggestions for how to
use it. Our favorite, though, is ``Pipe Cleaners Gone Crazy: A
Complete Guide to Bending Fuzzy Sticks.'' The step-by-step
instruction book comes with enough pipe cleaners to do every
project. All are appropriate for children of reading age; available
at children's bookstores. $13-$20. nn
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-06-28-99 1327EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
