</P>
<P>
   SCI-STEM-CELLS (Bethesda, Md.) _ The presidential bioethics
advisory commission struggles over the issue of whether federally
financed researchers should be allowed to obtain primordial human
cells from embryos. The cells offer potentially giant advantages in
treating a range of diseases, but opponents of abortion, among
others, say it is immoral to obtain them from embryos. By Nicholas
Wade.
</P>
<P>
   For other science and health stories, see the separate
SCIENCE-TIMES-BUDGET.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; FINANCIAL &LR;  (``f'' code)
</P>
<P>
   AUTO-UNION-SOUTH (Vance, Ala.) _ The United Automobile Workers
union is struggling to organize a Mercedes factory here. As auto
makers, especially foreign ones, expand in the American South, the
union may face more fights like the one shaping up in this unlikely
hotbed of union activity. By Robyn Meredith.
</P>
<P>
   With graphic.
