<P>
   MARKET (New York) _ At 11 a.m., stocks were higher. The Dow
Jones industrial average was up 1.3 percent, the S&AMP;P 500 up 1.25
percent and the Nasdaq composite index up 0.87 percent. The 30-year
bond was yielding 6.11 percent. European markets were mixed, with
London down 0.51 percent and Frankfurt up 1.05 percent. In Asia,
Japan's Nikkei closed up 1 percent, and the Hong Kong's Hang Seng
index closed up 0.4 of 1 percent. By Kenneth N. Gilpin.
</P>
