<P>
   HARTSFIELD-TROUBLE _ ATLANTA _ Bad day at Hartsfield, delays
running up to three hours, some cancelations. First, two aircraft
closed down two runways _ an AirTran jet slid off the runway and
then a Delta flight couldn't make a turn and a tug had to be
called. Then, a hard drive failed at the air traffic control center
and was down from 10 a.m. to 12:30 p.m., so the FAA slowed
everything down while a backup system took over. (Hendricks,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   BRIDGETT _ Readers from around the country were moved by a
Sunday AJC article depicting the struggle of a young black girl in
southwest Georgia. Callers from Oregon to Florida called the
newspaper saying they wanted to send clothes, books and money to
15-year-old Bridgett Stewart. Some drove hundreds of miles to
Preston, Ga., to talk to Bridgett and offer her encouragement.
(Dyer, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
