   IRELAND (Belfast) _ Hopes for breaking the deadlock in North
Ireland focus on a proposal to allow Protestants a token march
through a Catholic neighborhood in return for unionists dropping a
demand that the IRA begin disarming before Sinn Fein takes its seat
in the government. By Kevin Cullen and John O'Farrell. 900 words.
