<P>
   BC-KOSOVO-NATO-RUSSIA-NYT (moved on Friday, June 18)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Friday, June 18,
about NATO's military relations with Russia misstated the rank of
Col. Gen. Viktor M. Zavarzin, the commander of Russian peacekeepers
in Kosovo. His rank is three stars, not four, making him the
equivalent of a British or American lieutenant general.
</P>
