<HEADLINE>
SOME TRAVEL DEALS  
 (FOR RELEASE SUNDAY, JULY 4) 
</HEADLINE>
   (af)  
 By JANET PIORKO   
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   CABINS ON SALE
</P>
<P>
   Holland America is discounting three new cruises on the Maasdam
and one on the Rotterdam this summer and fall. The Maasdam's
seven-day sailing from London to Boston, departing Aug. 29, with
the Harry James Orchestra on board, ranges from $799 a person,
double occupancy, for an inside stateroom to $1,699 for a veranda
suite; its seven-day cruise from Boston to Montreal, departing
Sept. 5, costs $999 to $1,999, while a seven-day Eastern Caribbean
cruise departing Nov. 22 from Ft. Lauderdale is $799 to $1,699.
</P>
<P>
   On the Rotterdam, an eight-day cruise from Venice to Rome
departing Nov. 9 ranges from $999 to $1,999. Air fare is extra.
Information: (877) 724-5425. &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   SWINGING IN BOCA
</P>
<P>
   The Boca Raton Resort and Club has a Summer Value package
starting at $145 a night for a single or double room on Sunday
through Thursday, including unlimited greens fees (cart, which is
mandatory, is $25 a person extra) and tennis court time. (The top
price is $425 a night for an ocean-view suite in the Beach Club.) A
two-night minimum stay is required, with a nominal increase
(usually $5 a night) for Friday and Saturday. Tax of 10 percent and
service charge of $9.54 a day are extra. The resort has two 18-hole
golf courses, 30 tennis courts, several pools and a half-mile
beach. Information: (888) 495-2622. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   FLYING SOUTH
</P>
<P>
   Costa Rica and Rio de Janeiro are two of the destinations
offered by General Tours Expeditions in new Pricebuster packages.
</P>
<P>
   A six-night Costa Rica trip that spends three nights in San Jose
and three at Manuel Antonio National Park ranges from $799 (in
October and early November) to $1,099 (in late December), with many
departures priced in between; the price includes air fare on Delta
Airlines from Miami ($50 more round trip from New York).
</P>
<P>
   A five-night Rio trip including air fare from New York on United
or Delta starts at $679 a person, double occupancy, at the Luxor
Continental Hotel near Copacabana Beach, and goes up to $1,559 for
ocean-front accommodations at the Copacabana Palace. Those prices
are good through Dec. 16. Reservations: (800) 221-2216. &QL; 
