<SLUG> BC-FRIEDMAN-COLUMN-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
COMMENTARY: THIS IS THE BIG ONE 
</HEADLINE>
  (jt) 
 By THOMAS L. FRIEDMAN    
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   Memo to: President Mohammad Khatami of Iran &AMP; Prime Minister Zhu
Rongji of China From: President William J. Clinton
</P>
<P>
   Dear Gentlemen, I am writing to you both because though you may
not know it, you share the same problem, a serious problem, which
if not addressed effectively will become my problem. Quite simply,
you are both facing the biggest challenge ever from your domestic
opponents. This is the Big One for both of you. You run from this
challenge and your aspirations for your respective countries will
be squashed. It's that simple.
</P>
<P>
   President Khatami, let's start with you. Your hardline opponents
have ginned up this bogus allegation that 13 Iranian Jews have been
spying for Israel. We both know Israel would never be so crazy as
to use the tiny Jewish minority in Iran to do its spying. But we
also know why your opponents seized on this canard _ because it
puts you in an impossible position. If you defend these Iranian
Jews, your opponents will denounce you for protecting ``Zionist
agents''; and if you don't release them, and, God forbid, they are
executed, your whole strategy of improving Iran's relations with
the West _ beginning first with Western Europe and then with the
United States _ will be aborted.
</P>
<P>
   And let me assure you, if you kill these 13 Jews, Iran will be
treated as a pariah state like you've never seen. You and Slobodan
Milosevic and Saddam Hussein will be vacationing together for the
rest of your lives.
</P>
<P>
   We both know why this came up now. Iran will be holding its
parliamentary elections in March. President Khatami, you trounced
your opponents in the presidential election last year, winning 70
percent of the vote. But the hard-liners still control the
Parliament, the judiciary, the Revolutionary Guards and the
Intelligence Directorate. If you can win the Parliament in March,
your opponents will really be on the run, so they are using this
case to undermine you before the March runoff. But you still have
the mass base with you, and you need to rally them, in the streets
if need be, against those who want to use this spying case to cut
off Iran from the world. Tell the prosecutors that if there is
evidence of spying they must show it to the world. If not, Islamic
justice requires that the accused be set free.
</P>
<P>
   Prime Minister Zhu, the same goes for you. You know we bombed
your embassy in Belgrade by accident. And you know your domestic
opponents are keeping this thing alive to undermine all of those in
China who want to integrate with the world and with the United
States. I know you need to let off steam, but the steam can also
blow you away. When I read your recent Peoples Daily editorial
comparing the United States with ``Nazi Germany,'' it said to me
that your opponents are trying to stir up a level of
anti-Americanism not seen since the Cultural Revolution. And they
are doing it to make it impossible for you to make the concessions
needed for China to join the World Trade Organization _ which would
impose a set of global rules on China's trading practices that your
corrupt opponents have no interest in. I know you also have people
who sincerely want to restore the walls around China, to free it
from American domination and influence.
</P>
<P>
   But Zhu, there is no future in Chinese isolationism, and if you
don't take a stand against your opponents, if you are unable to
mobilize President Jiang and China's elites to complete this WTO
deal (you've stopped even returning our negotiators' phone calls),
you will never be able to accelerate economic reform as you aspire,
let alone attract sufficient foreign investment or participate in
the setting of global trading rules.
</P>
<P>
   I know what I am asking you means I've got to confront my own
domestic opponents, too. Zhu, you have my word that once you join
the WTO. I will bring China into the G-8 and make it the G-9, and
this time I won't shrink from getting Congress to ratify your WTO
membership. Mohammad, let me remind you again: the door is open for
normal relations between America and Iran. Yes, I am ready to lift
the sanctions on Iran and to take the measures that you have long
called for, such as settling outstanding financial claims. But I'm
not going to lift a finger for a rogue state that won't renounce
terrorism and kills innocent Jews. Like I said, guys, this is the
Big One for both of you. You run away from these challenges, you
turn the other cheek, you balk, you blink, you're finished.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
