   (NYT22) NEW YORK -- June 28, 1999 -- NY-CHAOS-FOR-A-DAY, 6-28 --
Police motorcycles, part of President Clinton's motorcade, are seen
parked near Times Square on Monday. President Clinton and some
corporate heavy hitters were attending a special matinee
performance nearby of the ``The Iceman Cometh.'' Some 113 years
ago, when the Statue of Liberty began advertising New York's
affection for huddled masses, no one probably envisioned just how
much of a multitude might show up one muggy day in midtown, or that
so many of them would come carrying cameras by car or stretch limo.
(James Estrin/New York Times Photo)
