<P>
   (NYT20) NEW YORK -- June 28, 1999 -- ELBAZ-FASHION-1, 6-28 -- A
satin evening dress was one of the styles modeled during an
informal show at Saks Fifth Avenue by Alber Elbaz, the new designer
of ready-to-wear for Yves Saint Laurent. Elbaz is walking a
tightrope without a net, attempting to breathe new life into a
40-year-old house that has just been Pinault-Printemps-Redoute
which plans to sell it to Gucci, which it also controls. That has
to worry the new designer on the block, especially a thin-skinned
one like Elbaz, who, in a low-key way, always seems anxious to
please. (Linda Rosier/New York Times Photo) LITE
</P>
<P>
   (NYT19) NEW YORK -- June 28, 1999 -- NY-HONDURAN-IMMIG, 6-28 --
Edwin Daniel Sabillion, 13, after in police custody on Monday.
Sabillion desperately wanted to leave his Honduran village,
devastated last year by Hurricane Mitch, to be with his father in
New York City. So his father sent him $200 and said to meet him at
LaGuardia Airport on June 28. Edwin hitchhiked and walked his way
north in a journey which took him a month. On Sunday, Sabillion
arrived in the city and asked a cab driver to take him to the
airport. The driver, thinking the boy was a runaway, called police.
Investigators are now trying to track down the boy's father, whose
phone number the boy had lost on his long journey northward. (Susan
B. Markisz/New York Times Photo) LITE
</P>
