COLO-SCHOOL-MURDERS-3, 6-28 -- Christopher Lau, 33, owner and
manager of Blackjack Pizza where both Eric Harris and Dylan Klebold
worked. Lau said the two had always seemed like normal high school
kids. ``It's now obvious they weren't,'' he said. (Kevin
Moloney/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT17) LITTLETON, Colo. -- June 28, 1999 --
COLO-SCHOOL-MURDERS-2, 6-28 -- A sign of support of for the parents
of Eric Harris outside their home in late April. On April 20, when
Harris and Dylan Klebold stormed into Columbine High School in this
Denver suburb and killed 12 classmates and a teacher, then
themselves, their parents suffered more than the loss of a child.
The boys' bombs and bullets shattered their parents' very view of
the world, undermining what had seemed to them and others to be18
