legislation. From right: Sens. Strom Thurmond, Jeff Sessions, Mike
Crapo, Craig Thomas, Larry Craig and Majority Leader Trent Lott.
(Paul Hosefros/New York Times)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT2) WASHINGTON -- June 28, 1999 -- BUDGET-CLINTON, 6-28 --
From left, Jacob Lew, director of the Office of Management and
Budget, Gene Sperling, chairman of the National Economic Council,
John Podesta, White House chief of staff, and Treasury Secretary
Robert Rubin, during a briefing on Monday about President Clinton's
budget surplus plans. Clinton proposed buttressing Social Security
and Medicare, using new White House projections that budget
surpluses will be more than $1 trillion bigger over the next 15
years than were envisioned earlier. (Justin Lane/New York Times
Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT1) WASHINGTON -- June 28, 1999 -- HUBBELL-STARR, 6-28 --
Webster Hubbell arrives to his home on Monday. Hubbell plans to
plead guilty Wednesday to a felony charge that he attempted to
cover up his and Hillary Rodham Clinton's role in a fraudulent
Arkansas land deal, legal sources said Monday. (Paul Hosefros/New
York Times Photo) LITE
</P>
