<HEADLINE>
GOOD HAIR DAY; SKIN TOO 
</HEADLINE>
  (sw) 
 By ANNE-MARIE SCHIRO   
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   With the coming Fourth of July holiday, summer weekending gets
into high gear with outings under the sun. Luckily, there are
beauty products designed to protect or enhance the skin and hair in
hot weather.
</P>
<P>
   For the hair, Frederic Fekkai has Sun Protectant spray and Hair
Mask ($22.50 each), at Saks Fifth Avenue, and Phytoplage has High
Protection Sun Oil ($19), Moisturing Sun Gel ($13) and After-Sun
Repair ($17), at Barneys New York.
</P>
<P>
   Barneys also has the Aesop Travel Survival Kit ($60), containing
two clay masks, a hydrator, ginger aromatherapy and a facial cream;
Foucaud's Liquid Body Lotion for heat rash ($20), and Nars Body
Glow, a skin bronzer ($55).
</P>
<P>
   Saks Fifth Avenue's choices include Clinique's oil-free City
Block for the face ($13.50); Osmotics Balancing Tonic Facial Mist
($35), to soothe and hydrate the face, even over makeup, and
Chanel's Sandals D'Or Goldlights, a shimmer gel for the face and
body ($22.50). &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
